universe of origin : intelligence without a brain
seal               : Not quite alive and not quite not — a virus is a scrap of genetic code in a protein shell that does nothing on its own, until it meets a cell. Then it hijacks the machinery of life to copy itself, evolves, adapts, and outnumbers every living thing on Earth. The clearest case of 'life-like' without being, settledly, alive.
